# Line-ending normalization.
#
# The repo is developed on a mix of Windows and Linux. core.autocrlf
# is set to `false` for this clone, which means whatever bytes are in
# a file at commit time are the bytes that end up in the git blob. For
# most files that is fine (Go is line-ending-agnostic), but shell
# scripts with a `\r` in the shebang line break on Linux:
#
#     /usr/bin/env: 'bash\r': No such file or directory
#
# ...which silently kills CI jobs. Forcing `*.sh` to LF at the blob
# level fixes this regardless of the contributor's local autocrlf
# setting, without forcing any change on working copies that are
# already LF.
#
# `*.py` gets the same treatment because our deploy scripts run on
# the VPS (Linux) and we ran into the same permission-denied class of
# bugs when Windows-created `.py` files were rsynced over.

*.sh      text eol=lf
*.py      text eol=lf
*.yml     text eol=lf
*.yaml    text eol=lf
Dockerfile text eol=lf
